name: Gladiators of Eden iPhone and iPad Game
blurb: Gladiators of Eden is a hybrid turn-based RPG battle style play game with casual land cultivation social game elements for iPhone/iPad.

rewards.reward: A free copy of the game plus a digital wallpaper featuring Gladiators of Eden.

Get the gift of weaponry!  We will send you a code to unlock a powerful weapon that will only be available to supporters.  We will also hook you up with the Digital wallpaper above and a copy of the game.

How about a one of a kind dragon pet that will only be available to kickstarter supporters.  The Genesis Dragon will be your way to show that you were a supporter of the Gladiators of Eden dream.  You also get the weapon and wallpaper.  Finally, Everyone who donates at this level or above will have their name put into the game as a kickstarter hero.  Thanks for helping make this dream a reality.
All the items above and a copy of the music from Gladiators of Eden on CD.  Matthew Pablo is an amazing composer and the music is going to be great.

A copy of original artwork signed by the Artists.  As you can see, the artwork is beautiful.  Candy and Kelly will personally sign copies of their original work.  You will also get all of the items above.  International shipping extra.

Beta Testing is so cool.  How about you help us build the best freaking game we can.  We will add you to the beta testers distribution list with weekly updates.  We will also set up a private message board to solicit input for features, creatures, and bugs, oh-my.  Plus, get everything above.  Wow, that's a lot of stuff.

We are proud of the artwork being developed and we are going to collect a bunch of concept and completed art and bind it up into a book.  International shipping extra.  Everything above included as well.  (Note: beta testing is limited so when I hit 80 above the $100 level I will be out of beta test slots.)

Indie Devs, spend a half hour speaking to a veteran iOS programmer and published author Steffen Itterheim.  He is the Author of the Learn and Master Cocos2D series of books and the creator of Kobold2D, a great extension to and wrapper of the Cocos2D game engine.

Get a phone conference with the Great Ray Wenderlich!  Get a 1/2 hour phone conference or technical consultation with Ray Wenderlich, an indie iOS developer who has co-authored two iOS development books and runs a popular iOS tutorial blog along with a team of fellow developers.  If you're looking to be an indie developer yourself, this might be a good way to get advice or your questions answered.  Ray can give advice on your game or app idea, answer technical questions, or talk about the indie life/entrepreneurship - whatever you like!  If you need to know how valuable this is, check out Ray's website at www.raywenderlich.com.  Also get the weaponry, digital wallpaper, and the signed copy of original artwork.

How about doing more than just giving feedback.  How about you help us design a significant weapon, spell, land, or event in the game.  We will setup a call with you and work together to define a significant item in the game.  We will acknowledge you in the credits as a design contributor as well as a kickstarter contributor.  You will get all of the items above as well.
